Create Victims Per Shooting by Month visual 14

Step 1. Use Line and Clustered Column Chart to create the visual


Steps

  1. Drag and drop Line and Clustered Column cart to an empty space on the canvas.
  2. Drag and drop the Date Hierarchy to the Shared Axis well. Remove other values from the hierarchy except MonthName and Days of the Week fields.
  3. Drag and drop Victims Per Shooting measure to the Column Values well.
  4. Drag and drop Average YOY measure to the Line Values well.


Step 2. Set the location and size of the visual


Steps

To adjust the size and location of the visual click on the visual, select the Format Pane and follow the steps below.

  1. Expand the General tab.
  2. Set the X Position to 742.
  3. Set the Y Position to 159.
  4. Set the Width to 740.
  5. Set the Height to 423.


Step 3. Format the X Axis


Steps

  1. Set the X Axis to On and Expand the X Axis to display the options.
  2. Set the color to Black or Hexadecimal 000000 and Text size to 12.
  3. Set the Minimum Category Width to 20 and Maximum Size to 15%.
  4. Set the Inner Padding to 10% and we will set the axis title to Off to save space.


Step 4. Format the Y Axis

Steps

  1. Set the Y Axis to On,  Expand the Y Axis to display the options and set the color to Hexadecimal CC9900.
  2. Set the Text size to 12 turn the Title Off and turn the Gridlines On.
  3. Set the Gridlines color to Black, set Stroke Width to 1 and set the Line Style to Dotted.
  4. Set the Y Axis (Line) color to Hexadecimal 118DFF and set the Text Size to 12 Points.


Step 5. Format the Data Colors

Steps

  1. Set the Average YOY (the Line chart) color to Hexadecimal 007FFF.
  2. Set the Default Color (the Column chart) color to Hexadecimal CC9900.

Step 6. Format the Data Labels

6.1 Format the Line Values Data Labels


Steps

  1. Turn the Data Labels to On and set (the Line chart) data color to Hexadecimal 007FFF.
  2. Set the Display Units to Auto and Value Decimal Places to 1.
  3. Set the Orientation to Horizontal and the Position to Inside End.
  4. Set the Text Size to 14.


6.2. Format the Column values Data Labels


Steps

  1. Set the Column Value (Victims Per Shooting) data color to Hexadecimal CC9900.
  2. Set the Display Units to Auto and Value Decimal Places to 0.
  3. Set the data labels Position to Outside End.
  4. Set the Text Size to 14.
  5. Turn the Show Background to On.
  6. Set the Background color to White and set the Transparency to 18%.

Step 7. Format Shapes option

Steps

  1. Expand the Shapes tab to display the options and turn the Shade Area On.
  2. Set the Stroke Width to 3, Join Type to Round and Line Style to Solid.
  3. Turn Off the Show Marker and Stepped buttons.

Step 8. Format title of visual

Steps

We use the Format pane to format the visual title.

  1. Set the Title to On and expand the Title option.
  2. Insert Victims Per Shooting by Month  into the Title Text box.
  3. Set the font color to White and set the background color to Hexadecimal 007FFF.
  4. Set the title alignment to center and text size to 18 pt.

This is youtube video on how to create a Column and Line chart visualization.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wr2vA3lGK8w
